    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but what about the people who say a sudden influx messes up the local economy by driving down wages for the existing working class? if that's a real concern for a lot of people, wouldn't that mean the \"net positive\" argument is kind of ignoring a huge part of the actual economic reality on the ground?",
