      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concern about wage depression is a legitimate, albeit often overstated, fear that focuses on the short-term, low-skilled segments of the labor market. While some localized wage pressures can occur, the overwhelming evidence shows that the overall economic gains from increased productivity and labor supply outweigh these localized effects. The \"net positive\" argument is not ignoring reality; it is focusing on the macroeconomic trends that drive national prosperity, which are fundamentally positive.",
